cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on Part-of-Speech (PoS) tagging for code-mixed Indian social media text. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with NLP and related topics. The use of a Conditional Random Field classifier also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also deals with feature extraction, which is a common topic in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories.
